Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat. Add tomato, red bell pepper, onion, zucchini, and mushrooms; cook and stir until tender, about 5 minutes. Add rice, ketchup, bacon, paprika, salt, and black pepper; stir well to combine. Transfer to serving plate. Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat. Pour in eggs in a thin layer; cook until set, about 5 minutes. Serve eggs over rice mixture.